                        "correctFeedback": "Perfect! The function counts items using accumulation.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Use + to increment count by 1.",
                        "explanation": "Accumulating in a loop is a common pattern in functions.",
                        "output": "3"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "building_lists",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Functions can build new lists by starting with an empty list and adding items one by one."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Create empty list `[]` → Loop through items → Process each item → Append to the new list → Return the new list."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def double_numbers(numbers):\n    result = []\n    for num in numbers:\n        result.append(num * 2)\n    return result\n\ndoubled = double_numbers([1, 2, 3, 4])\nprint(doubled)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "[2, 4, 6, 8]"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Start with empty `result` list. For each number, multiply it by 2 and `append` to `result`. After processing all numbers, return the new list."
                }
            ]
        },
