        {
            "id": "searching_in_loops",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Searching with Loops",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Functions can search through lists using loops. When you find what you're looking for, `return` immediately - no need to keep checking!"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def find_name(names, target):\n    for name in names:\n        if name == target:\n            return True\n    return False\n\npeople = [\"Alice\", \"Bob\", \"Charlie\"]\nprint(find_name(people, \"Bob\"))\nprint(find_name(people, \"Dan\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "True\nFalse"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The loop checks each name. If it matches `target`, return `True` immediately and exit. If the loop finishes without finding it, return `False`."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "`return` inside a loop exits the entire function right away. This saves time - no need to check remaining items once you found what you need."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_search",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "What happens when the function finds what it's searching for?"
                },
                {
                    "type": "mcq",
                    "content": "",
                    "properties": {
                        "question": "",
                        "options": [
                            "It continues checking all items",
                            "It returns immediately and exits",
                            "It stores the result and continues"
                        ],
                        "correctAnswerIndex": 1,
                        "correctFeedback": "Correct! return exits the loop and function immediately.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "return exits the function right away when the item is found.",
                        "explanation": "Using return in a loop lets you exit early when you find what you need."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "while_loops",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Functions can use `while` loops when you want to repeat something until a condition changes."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def count_down(start):\n    while start > 0:\n        print(start)\n        start = start - 1\n    print(\"Done!\")\n\ncount_down(3)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "3\n2\n1\nDone!"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Print the current value of `start`, then decrease it by 1. Keep repeating while `start > 0`. When `start` reaches 0, the loop stops and `\"Done!\"` prints."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_while",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "code_fill",
                    "content": "Fill in the missing operator to add up numbers from 1 to n using a while loop.",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "lines": [
                            {
                                "code": "def sum_up_to(n):",
                                "indent": 0
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "    total = 0",
                                "indent": 0
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "    while n > 0:",
                                "indent": 0
