                        },
                        "hint": "Add n to total each time to get the sum.",
                        "correctFeedback": "Great job! This sums numbers from 1 to n.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Use + to add up the numbers.",
                        "explanation": "A while loop can be used to add numbers repeatedly until n reaches 0.",
                        "output": "10"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "range_in_functions",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Remember `range()`? It creates a sequence of numbers. You can use it in functions to repeat something a specific number of times."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "def repeat_message(message, times):\n    for i in range(times):\n        print(message)\n\nrepeat_message(\"Hello\", 3)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "Hello\nHello\nHello"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "`range(times)` creates numbers from `0` to `times-1`. The loop runs that many times, printing the message each time."
                }
            ]
        },
